You are here:

Chart Formatting Options

Control the appearance and behavior of your chart.

FIELD	DESCRIPTION
Chart Title	Enter a name for the chart.
Title Color	Select the color for the text of your chart title.
Text Color	Select a color for all the text and labels in your chart.
Background Fade	Choose a direction for a gradient color background. Also select a Start Color and End Color for the gradient.
Legend Position	Choose a place to display the legend in relation to your chart.
Combine Small Groups into “Others”	Combine all groups less than or equal to 3% of the total into a single “Others” wedge or segment.
X- or Y-Axis Range	Choose a manual or automatic axis range for bar, line, or column charts.
Show Axis Labels	Display labels for each axis of your chart.
Show Values	Display the values of individual records or groups on the chart.
Chart Size	Select a size for the chart, from Tiny to Extra Large.
Chart Position	Place the chart above or below your report.
